Answer:
Antipattern Detected: Functional Decomposition: Using the include relationship

   Constructs Involved: Book Grooming Appointment, Select Time Slot
   Explanation: The use case "Select Time Slot" is an inclusion use case that is included by only one use case ("Book Grooming Appointment"). "Select Time Slot" is not associated with any actor directly, does not include or extend any other use case, is not extended by any use case, and is not involved in any generalization. It represents a sub-step of booking rather than a complete, independently valuable service. Selecting a time slot alone provides no observable result to the user — it only makes sense as part of the booking process. This is a textbook example of functional decomposition where a single use case's internal logic has been artificially split into a separate inclusion use case.
